Highly disagree with the translator's stance on the irrelevance of netori and netorare. Implying that they're both the same thing is a glaring sign that they're not familiar with the genre at all. Netorare is made with the intent of fetishizing the feeling of jealousy/anger that the author tries to invoke from the reader. Netori, on the other hand, is a power fantasy where the reader feels like the one doing the cucking. Both genres are fundamentally different. These nuances are the exact reason why NTR is even a thing. If we discard those nuances, we might as well just abandon the tag.
